4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would exempt Precision Ocular from the
6 payment of state sales and use taxes for five years.
7 This bill would also allow municipalities and
8 counties to exempt this entity from local sales and use
9 taxes.
10
11
12 A BILL
13 TO BE ENTITLED
14 AN ACT
15
16 Relating to sales and use taxes; to exempt Precision
17 Ocular from payment of state sales and use taxes; and to allow
18 municipalities and counties to exempt this entity from local
19 sales and use taxes.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. (a) For the period commencing on October 1,
22 2026, and ending on September 30, 2031, unless extended by an
23 act of the Legislature, Precision Ocular is exempt from paying
24 any state sales and use taxes.
25 (b) Precision Ocular may be exempted from paying county
26 and municipal sales and use taxes upon approval of the county
27 or municipality pursuant to Section 40-23-4.01, Code of
28 Alabama 1975.
